Changes from the original:

Builder (builder/src/build_index.cpp):
- S2Builder polygon repair pipeline (three-tier: S2Loop > S2Builder > bbox fallback)
- Configurable simplification limit via --max-vertices flag (default 50,000, was hardcoded 500)
- Lenient libosmium multipolygon assembly (ignore_invalid_locations)
- Node location handler error tolerance (ignore_errors)
- In-memory node location index (--in-memory flag, SparseMemArray)
- Pass 1.5 node filtering: bitmap-based pre-scan skips 89% of nodes, reducing
  SparseMemArray from ~134 GB to ~11 GB for planet builds
- Flat sorted pair vectors replacing all cell hash maps (unordered_map<uint64_t,
  vector<uint32_t>> replaced with packed 12-byte CellEntry vectors), reducing
  cell structure memory from ~37 GB to ~5.5 GB at planet scale
- Write phase optimization: std::set replaced with vector+sort+unique, hash map
  offset tables replaced with position-indexed vectors, progressive memory
  release with malloc_trim(0), merge-scan writes replacing hash lookups
- Live memory diagnostics (/proc/self/status RSS/Swap/VM at each phase)
- Temp file directory override (--tmpdir flag)
- Skip PBF metadata parsing (read_meta::no)
- Reuse S2RegionCoverer instances (static initialization)
- Highway filter using unordered_set (O(1) lookup)
- Vector pre-allocation from PBF file size heuristics with shrink_to_fit
  before writing to reclaim over-reserved capacity
- Per-phase build timers and throughput reporting
- Diagnostic counters and --verbose/--debug flags

Server (server/src/main.rs):
- Country-boundaries fallback for missing country data in continent/regional
  PBF extracts (overseas territories of France, Spain, Netherlands)
- --no-country-fallback flag to disable fallback for planet builds
- Precomputed mmap slice lengths at load time
- Eliminated redundant Vec allocation in cell neighbor lookup
- Fixed street deduplication hash collisions in dense areas
- Rewrote format_address to use single String buffer
- Fixed rate limiter race condition (atomics replaced with Mutex)
- Rate limiter: 0 means unlimited (restored upstream semantics)
- Added bounds checking on all mmap slice accesses
- Input validation for lat/lon parameters
- Applied clippy lints and rustfmt formatting
- Updated TLS dependencies for security fixes (RUSTSEC-2026-0044,
  RUSTSEC-2026-0048, RUSTSEC-2026-0049)
- 40 unit tests (format_address, auth, rate limiter, coordinates, fallback)

Server (server/src/main.rs) -- correctness review:
- Fixed house number interpolation: switched from squared distances to true
  arc lengths (sqrt) for path position ratios, correcting a bias toward
  longer segments in unequal-length interpolation ways
- Doc comments on dist_sq explaining equirectangular approximation, error
  bounds at all latitudes (sub-meter at 75m radius even at 85N), and proof
  that the approximation is conservative (no false negatives)
- Doc comments on point_in_polygon explaining f32 precision adequacy for
  admin boundaries and vertical edge safety
- Doc comments on seen_streets direct-mapped cache explaining idempotency
  and collision behavior
- Analytical tests: dist_sq vs haversine error table, conservative search
  radius proof, interpolation sqrt vs squared ratio verification
- 43 unit tests (was 40)

Server (server/src/auth.rs):
- #[serde(default)] on users and tokens fields
- Applied clippy lints and rustfmt formatting

Licensing:
- Apache 2.0 copyright headers added to all source files per Section 4(b)
- SPDX-License-Identifier tags on build_index.cpp, main.rs, auth.rs
